The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | City bid for Berbatov
                                                                                                                                                                                                     City bid for Berbatov
            IN amp; OUT                
	 Manchester City have made a 25m bid for Tottenham striker Dimitar Berbatov, the clubs prospective new owners said Monday. A late attempt was launched to hijack cross-town rival Manchester Uniteds long-running pursuit of Berbatov before the transfer window closed at midnight local time.         
	Spurs recruits         
	 Tottenham Hotspur completed the signings of Croatia defender Vedran Corluka and Russia striker Roman Pavlyuchenko on Monday. The club said that they had paid Spartak Moscow euros 17m for the 26-year-old Pavlyuchenko, who has signed a five-year contract. Corluka, who handed in a transfer request to Premier League rivals Manchester City, agreed a six-year contract after his 8.5m switch to the London club.         
	Inter sign Quaresma         
	 Jose Mourinhos Inter Milan have agreed to sign Portugal winger Ricardo Quaresma from Porto on a three-year contract for a total of euros 24.6m, Porto said in a statement on Sunday.         
	Reds buy Riera         
	lLiverpool signed Spanish winger Albert Riera from Espanyol on Monday. The 26-year-old, who had a brief spell in England with Manchester City, has agreed to a four-year contract although no details of the transfer fee were disclosed.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                        
